fix(storage): remove legacy ACL usage for GCS uniform bucket access

Removed `public: true` option from GCS file upload as it's incompatible
with uniform bucket-level access (which is now the default on GCS).

Instead, the bucket should be configured with public access at the bucket
level using IAM permissions (allUsers with Storage Object Viewer role).

This resolves the "Cannot insert legacy ACL" error during photo uploads.
